# MyList Admin UI Coding Rules

## Core Structure
- Keep route paths centralized in `src/routes/paths.ts` and route mapping in `src/routes/routes.tsx`.
- Add each new page under `src/pages/<ModuleName>/` and expose from barrel files where used.
- Reusable UI belongs in `src/components/`; business-specific UI stays inside its module.
- Put shared constants in `src/constants/`, shared types in `src/types/`, and shared helpers in `src/helpers/`.

## Coding Style
- Prefer TypeScript-first patterns with explicit domain types and avoid `any`.
- Reuse existing app providers and patterns from `src/main.tsx` (`Apollo`, router, theme, i18n).
- Keep component logic and style colocated (`<Page>.tsx` + `<Page>.style.ts`) for page-level screens.
- Use store hooks from `src/store/` for global state and local `useState` for local UI state.

## Routing and Access
- When adding features, update both `paths` and `routes` files together.
- Use role-aware route configuration (`allowedRoles`) for private pages.
- Preserve auth flow in `App.tsx` (unauthenticated users must go to sign-in).

## Delivery Checklist
- Add/update types, constants, and helpers before duplicating logic in pages.
- Keep imports clean with existing aliases and project conventions.
- Ensure `pnpm lint` and `pnpm build` stay clean after changes.
